	<h4>Describe the three components of the HTML document (HTML, CSS, JavaScript).</h4>
	<p><font color="red"> A starting tag 
Body or the content 
An ending tag
</font></p>

	<br>
	<h4>Name and describe four distinct HTML tags.</h4>
	<p><font color="red"><html>  This defines an HTML document
<head>  it defines the head of the document. This is where the document starts
<title>   It defines title for the document
<body> It defines body of the document. It basically contains all the document.
</font></p>

	<br>
	<h4>Identify an HTML tag that does not require an end tag.</h4>
	<p><font color="red">This is some text!</font></p>
Empty elements in html does not rquire end tag
"<br>" is an example of this. It is used for line break.

	<br>
	<h4>Read this page on <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_syntax.asp" target="_blank">CSS Syntax</a> then name and describe element selectors, id selectors, and class selectors.</h4>
	<p><font color="red"> Element selectors uses name of the element to select. For example if we have to select <p> element which is for paragraph we use 
p {
}
We can put what we want between the curly brackets. For example 
P {
text-align: center;
    color: red;
}
This will make the paragraph centrally aligned with red font.

Id selector
It is used to select one unique element as it uses id attribute of an element.
Hash (#) character is used to do this. For example #para. Para is an element here.
</font></p>

	<br>
